{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make dog theft a specific criminal offence",
        "additional_details": "There have been reports of substantial increases in dog theft in recent months, with the most loyal of animals torn away from its family. Thieves think it\u2019s all too easy and the punishment can be nothing compared to the gain with a shocking minority of dogs being reunited with their families.\r\nDog theft is not currently a specific offence and the crime of theft carries a sentence of up to seven years according to the Theft Act 1968, but this doesn\u2019t target the specific problem which is dog theft.\r\n \r\nDogs should be seen to have their own offence to protect them. Current laws and penalties are not enough justice for the families and dogs that go through this trauma. They protect us, so we will protect them.",
        "background": "The Government should create a specific offence for dog theft, with 8 years minimum sentencing and a fine of at least \u00a35,000. Dogs are like members of the family to many people and current laws do not reflect this. Dogs are a support network for so many, a family member, a lifeline.",
